Phone: ||1) It's near to Wakaf Che Yeh, where the night markets are.  You just need to cross the road.||2) Room is spacious.||||What's bad about this hotel:||||1)  Hygiene and cleanliness! This is the biggest problem.  It seems as if this hotel doesn't have a proper maintenance / cleaning crew.  ||||As you walk into the lobby, you notice muddy shoe prints on the tiled floor.  The indoor swimming pool to your left is filled with murky green water.  It's like they're giving you signs of what's to come. ||||Once you're in your room, the toilet greets you with a strong and funky smell.  It smells of mold, it smells of someone not cleaning the toilet properly.  And you could see the brown yellowish mold at the corners of the floor, walls and edges of the sink.  The chrome taps and bidet are covered in water spots, another indication that the cleaner did not do his/her job properly.  The toilet bowl is filled with brown water, which you are then required to flush first before doing your business.  You have to do all this quickly though, as the smell is too overpowering.  As you rush out of the toilet and lie down on the bed, you realise that you will have to shower in that despicable toilet soon.  You've made a mistake for booking this hotel.  Let that sink in.||||2)  The location of the hotel is not so strategic if you go to the city center a lot.  Wakaf Che Yeh is the only attraction that's just across the main road...and a McDonald's...if you're that kind of traveler. ||||3)  Gym's a joke.  It's outside the hotel near the trash area.  And it only has a treadmill and a stationary bike.  Plus the room smells of, you've guess it, mold.  ||||4)  Do a bit of exploring and observing around the hotel and you will see the disorganization of the place i.e boxes stacked up against the wall near the conference room, papers littered on the front desk etc.||||5)  WiFi is weak. ||||Conclusion:||||I don't mean to bash this place so much.  But what would all this say about the kind of culture the hotel is practicing?  The state of cleanliness alone gave me doubts about their breakfast spread in the morning, of which I went out to have instead.  How could I trust their food hygiene is their overall hygiene is disappointing?  I just hope the hotel will improve on this.
